d it rely on `metadata.dir`? There’s a chance native might fail if there's no metadata. Even though I think 4.1.5-dev metadata isn't required, it seems the test source does have it in `gradle.properties`. Yet, I realize that without the old metadata, specific tests will fail. I should consider if I can use the default dependency 4.1.5 instead.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented the fix in:\n\n- `tests/src/avalon-framework/avalon-framework/4.1.5-dev/build.gradle`\n\nChange made:\n- Mapped the non-published test metadata version `4.1.5-dev` to the published Maven artifact version `4.1.5` for dependency resolution.\n- Kept the existing Java test coverage unchanged.\n\nValidation run successfully:\n\n- `./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=avalon-framework:avalon-framework:4.1.5-dev --stacktrace`\n- `./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=avalon-framework:avalon-framework:4.1.5-dev --stacktrace`\n- `./gradlew nativeTest -Pcoordinates=avalon-framework:avalon-framework:4.1.5-dev --stacktrace`\n\nAll passed.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0cc59499cf708cf10169f625c854ac81a3a1a5b30055f2da46\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 681, "output": 692, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36189, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777739198654, "responseId": "resp_0cc59499cf708cf10169f625bf1e9481a38ddf90486b850173"}, "toolResults": []}
